		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One thing I've always found kind of odd was how they had so many frames of animation. Even with Donkey Kong Land on GB, everything moves so smoothly.
<br />
<br />I would think they use some sort of compression, either that or they reuse the tiles REALLY intelligently.
<br />
<br />As a side note, you say it's 32 megabit. I don't mean to be an ass, but why not say it's 4 Megabytes? What's so special about a megabit anyways?

		

		</td>
